              <td height="100%" align="left" valign="top" background="images/hkix_logo_04.jpg" style="background-repeat:no-repeat "><table width=800 border=0 cellpadding="5" cellspacing=0 bgcolor="#333333">
                <tr>
                  <td height="24" colspan="2" valign="top" bgcolor="#666666" class="title"><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="header" -->&nbsp;Data Centre Policy <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></td>
                </tr>
                <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="content" -->
                <tr bordercolor="#666666">
                  <td colspan="2" valign="top" background="images/hkix_bg_policies.jpg" style="background-repeat:no-repeat" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="normaltext"><table width="97%"  border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td><p>HKIX – Data Centre Policy   (hereinafter refer to as the   “Policy”)</p>
                        <p class="header"><strong>Definition</strong></p>
                        <TABLE cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="0" border="0">
                          <TBODY>
                            <TR>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="103"><p><strong><em>ITSC</em></strong></p>
                                  <p><strong><em> </em></strong></p></TD>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="477"><p>Refers   to Information Technology Services Centre of the Chinese University of Hong   Kong</p>
                                  <p> </p></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="103"><p><strong><em>Data Centre</em></strong></p></TD>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="477"><p>Refers   to the HKIX-1 data centre located within ITSC Central Computer Room  at  Pi Chiu Building of the Chinese University of Hong Kong.</p>
                                  <p> </p></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="103"><p><strong><em>Customer    </em></strong></p></TD>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="477"><p>Refers   to an organization that has connected to HKIX facilities or has equipment   collocated at the HKIX Data Centre.</p>
                                  <p> </p></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="103"><p><strong><em>Licensed Area</em></strong></p></TD>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="477"><p>Refers   to that portion of   the Data Centre made available by HKIX to the Customer for the placement of   Customer's equipment and use of the Data Centre Services.</p>
                                  <p> </p></TD>
                            </TR>
                            <TR>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="103"><p><strong><em>Representatives</em></strong></p></TD>
                              <TD vAlign="top" width="477"><p>Refers   to those   individuals identified in writing by the Customer on the HKIX Data Centre Access Authorization List Form.</p></TD>
                            </TR>
                          </TBODY>
                        </TABLE>
                        <p> </p>
                        <p class="header"><strong>Site   Access</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                          <li>Only those Representatives identified in   writing by the Customer on the HKIX Data Centre Access Authorization List Form may make   request to enter the Data Centre.</li>
                          <li>For every Data Centre visit, a maximum   of<strong><em> 3</em></strong> persons,   of whom at least one must be a Representative, may enter the Data Centre at the   same time. For security reasons, all visitors (Representatives and accompanying   persons) will be requested to show his/her STAFF ID and HKID (or Passport) for   verification. He/she will be refused to enter the Data Centre if the required   credentials cannot be shown.</li>
                          <li>HKIX reserves the right not to allow   entrance to the Data Centre if the Data Centre already has too many companies   performing works.</li>
                          <li>Customer shall deliver prior written   notice to HKIX of any changes in the list of Representatives through the HKIX Data Centre Access Authorization List Form.</li>
                          <li>Customer and its Representatives may only   enter its licensed area, unless otherwise approved and accompanied by an   authorized HKIX’s representative.</li>
                          <li>Customer has full responsibility and   liability for all acts or omissions of Representatives and accompanying persons   and all such acts or omissions will be attributed to Customer for all purposes,   including for the purposes of determining whether Customer has breached this   Policy.</li>
                          <li>Each Customer must ensure that the   Representatives and the accompanying persons do not take any actions that   Customer is prohibited from taking under this Policy.</li>
                          <li>Customer must provide HKIX with at least <strong><em>(1)   one</em></strong> working day prior notice via e-mail any time it intends to access the HKIX Data   Centre. </li>
                          <li>Customer must provide HKIX with at least <strong><em>(3)   three</em></strong> working days prior notice any time it requires on site technical support at the   HKIX Data Centre or it intends to move-in or move-out any Customer   Equipment.</li>
                          <li>The Representatives must fill in the   details for access in the HKIX Data Centre Access Form before they enter the   Data Centre.</li>
                          <li>The Representatives and the accompanying   persons must wear their staff ID cards and our visitor cards within the HKIX   Data Centre.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p class="header"><strong>Conduct at the Data   Centre</strong></p>
                        <ol>
                          <li>The Representatives and the accompanying   persons must keep its licensed area as well as HKIX Data Centre clean and tidy   at all times.</li>
                          <li>The Representatives and the accompanying   persons agree to adhere to and abide by all security and safety measures   established by HKIX. </li>
                          <li>The Representatives and the accompanying   persons must refrain from doing the following:
                            <ol type="a">
                              <li>engage in any activity that is in   violation of the laws or aids or assists any criminal activity while at HKIX   property or in connection with the Data Centre Services;</li>
                              <li> misuse or abuse any HKIX’s property or   equipment or third party equipment;</li>
                              <li>make any unauthorized use of or interfere   with any property or equipment of any other customer;</li>
                              <li>harass any individual, including HKIX   personnel and representatives of other customers; and</li>
                              <li>use of any photographic, video, film or   such other device that produces, reproduces, retains or transmits images within   the premises and the licensed space.</li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>Customer must not, except as otherwise   agreed by HKIX,
                            <ol type="i"><li>place any computer hardware or   other equipment in the Licensed Area</li>
                              <li>store any other combustible   materials of any kind in the Licensed Area; and </li>
                              <li>bring any “Prohibited   Materials” (as defined below) into the Data Centre. Prohibited Materials shall   include, but not limited to, the following and any similar items:
                                <ol>
                                    <ol type="a">
                                      <li>Food, drink, illegal drugs and other   intoxicants</li>
                                      <li>Tobacco products</li>
                                      <li> Explosives and weapons</li>
                                      <li> Hazardous materials</li>
                                      <li> Electro-magnetic devices, which could   unreasonably interfere with computer and telecommunications equipment</li>
                                      <li> Radioactive materials</li>
                                      <li>Photographic or recording equipment of any   kind</li>
                                      <li>Any other items deemed inappropriate at   HKIX’s sole discretion.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                </ol>
                              </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <li>All of Customer’s equipment must be   installed, operated, configured and run at all times in compliance with the   manufacturer's specifications, including power outlet, power consumption and   clearance requirements and the applicable laws. </li>
                          <li>All Customer’s Equipment must be put   within HKIX’s licensed area, and they must be either rack-mounted, or be put on   HKIX’s provided fixed partitions. None of Customer’s equipment is allowed to   stack or rest on the equipment of any other Customer;</li>
                          <li>All of the cables and wiring in Customer’s   licensed area must be neatly labeled, wrapped and tied together (if a customer   fails to do so, HKIX may in its sole option neatly wrap and tie such wires and   cables, and HKIX may charge the customer for performing such   service);</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p class="header"><strong>Electrical Power</strong></p>
                        <ol><li>Each of HKIX’s standard cabinet is   provisioned for 13A power consumption, and the maximum number of power sockets   allowed are that previously agreed by HKIX. The Customer could only use those   power sockets as assigned by HKIX.</li>
                          <li>It is the Customer’s sole responsibility   to ensure that the power provided as agreed by HKIX is sufficient to power the   devices for regular use.</li>
                          <li>HKIX may independently inspect the power   configuration of any cabinet with Customer’s licensed space, at any time. </li>
                          <li>HKIX may direct Customer
                            <ol type="a">
                              <li>to alter the power   configuration of Customer’s equipment; </li>
                              <li> to disconnect power supply to   the Customer’s equipment; or </li>
                              <li>require Customer to remove from   any equipment, if HKIX considers that the continued operation of Customer’s   equipment: </li>
                            </ol>
                          </li>
                          <ol>
                            <ol type="i">
                              <li>causes a threat to safety to the   operations of HKIX’s Data Centre or the Data Centre property;</li>
                                  <li> unreasonably interferes with the   operations of HKIX, any other customer or any entity utilizing any portion of   the Data Centre; </li>
                                  <li>is not installed in accordance with   standard industry practice; and/or</li>
                                  <li> is consuming or has consumed excessive   power.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </ol>
                          <li>HKIX reserves the right to disconnect any   unauthorized power connection made by Customers without notice.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p class="header"><strong>Remarks</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>If   Customer breaches any of the terms mentioned in this policy, HKIX reserves the   rights to suspend or to disconnect the services partly or wholly, or restrict   Customer or its Representatives from accessing the licensed area without   incurring any liabilities or obligations.</strong></p>
                        <p>HKIX   may change this Policy from time to time and the revised Policy shall be posted   at HKIX Homepage at <A href="http://www.hkix.net/">http://www.hkix.net</A>.   Customer is required to review HKIX’s website regularly to keep itself informed   of the most current version of this Policy at all times</p></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>                  <p class="normaltext">&nbsp;</p>
                  <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
